usdAtmMIB.name: usdAtmMIB

revisions.description: Added support for CAC used bandwidth. Added ATM switched virtual connection (SVC) support. Added usdAtmSubIfAddress to the usdAtmSubIfTable.
Added support for connection admission control (CAC).
Added support from ATM traffic shaping.

Added support for NBMA map lists. Added support for ATM ping. Changed usdAtmSubIfVccVcd and usdAtmIfIlmiVcd range to (0..2147483647). Added range to usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd. Added rtVbr service catagory to usdAtmSubIfVccTable. Added support for OAM cell filter. Added PVC counter for reveived unknown protocol.
Added autoconfig value for usdAtmSubIfVccType. Added in/out summary cell counters. Added usdVpTunnelServiceCategory to usdAtmVpTunnelTable. Added support for atm interface capability traversal.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdAtmMIB.description: The ATM MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

UsdAtmNbmaMapName.name: UsdAtmNbmaMapName
UsdAtmNbmaMapName.description: An administratively assigned map name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set. The name must be unique per system.
UsdAtmNbmaMapName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

UsdAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.name: UsdAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull
UsdAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.description: An administratively assigned map name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set. The name must be unique per system. Differs from UsdAtmNbmaMapName in that it permits a zero-length string.
UsdAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

usdAtmNextIfIndex.name: usdAtmNextIfIndex
usdAtmNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdAtmIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdAtmIfTable.name: usdAtmIfTable
usdAtmIfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM interfaces present in the system.

usdAtmIfEntry.name: usdAtmIfEntry
usdAtmIfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdAtmIfIndex.name: usdAtmIfIndex
usdAtmIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdAtmNextIfIndex.

usdAtmIfRowStatus.name: usdAtmIfRowStatus
usdAtmIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdAtmIfRowStatus usdAtmIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for usdAtmIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdAtmNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdAtmIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdAtmIfLowerIfIndex
usdAtmIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this ATM interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdAtmIfIlmiVpi.name: usdAtmIfIlmiVpi
usdAtmIfIlmiVpi.description: The VPI of the ILMI of a major ATM interface.

usdAtmIfIlmiVci.name: usdAtmIfIlmiVci
usdAtmIfIlmiVci.description: The VCI of the ILMI of a major ATM interface.

usdAtmIfIlmiVcd.name: usdAtmIfIlmiVcd
usdAtmIfIlmiVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ILMI, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. The value must be unique among VCs configured on the same ATM interface.

usdAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency.name: usdAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency
usdAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency.description: The amount of time in seconds between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting loss of ILMI connectivity. The distinguished value zero disables ILMI connectivity procedures on this interface.

usdAtmIfIlmiAdminState.name: usdAtmIfIlmiAdminState
usdAtmIfIlmiAdminState.description: The administrative status of ILMI in the ATM interface.

usdAtmIfUniVersion.name: usdAtmIfUniVersion
usdAtmIfUniVersion.description: Use to specify the User Network Interface (UNI) the router should use when ILMI link auto determination is unsuccesful or ILMI is disabled.

usdAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState.name: usdAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState
usdAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState.description: Use to specify the OAM Cell Receive Administrative state on this interface.

usdAtmIfInCells.name: usdAtmIfInCells
usdAtmIfInCells.description: The total number of cells received on this major interface.

usdAtmIfOutCells.name: usdAtmIfOutCells
usdAtmIfOutCells.description: The total number of cells transmitted on this major interface.

usdAtmIfVcCount.name: usdAtmIfVcCount
usdAtmIfVcCount.description: The total number of circuits configured on this interface.

usdAtmIfMapGroup.name: usdAtmIfMapGroup
usdAtmIfMapGroup.description: The NBMA map group this interface is associated with.

usdAtmIfCacAdminState.name: usdAtmIfCacAdminState
usdAtmIfCacAdminState.description: The administrative staus of CAC on this ATM major interface.

usdAtmIfCacUbrWeight.name: usdAtmIfCacUbrWeight
usdAtmIfCacUbrWeight.description: The bandwidth associated with every UBR and UBR with PCR connection configured on the ATM major interface. This value is used for CAC computation. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

usdAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth.name: usdAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth
usdAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth.description: The subscribed bandwidth of the ATM major interface. If this value is not specified or set to 0, the effective port bandwidth is used. When a Get operation is performed the current effective bandwidth is returned. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

usdAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth.name: usdAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth
usdAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth.description: The available bandwidth of the ATM major interface. As connections are added or deleted on the interface, this value is updated. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

usdAtmIfOamCellFilter.name: usdAtmIfOamCellFilter
usdAtmIfOamCellFilter.description: The type of OAM cells to discard when usdAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState is set to oamCellAdminStateDisabled. The value oamCellFilterAlarm discards received OAM AIS and RDI cells. The value oamCellFilterAll discards all received OAM cells. Note that when usdAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState is set to oamCellAdminStateEnabled, this object has no effect.

usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.name: usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper
usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.description: The most significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth on the ATM major interface. The least significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth are specified by usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.

usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.name: usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower
usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.description: The least significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth on the ATM major interface. The most significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth are specified by usdAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.

usdAtmPvcStatisticsTable.name: usdAtmPvcStatisticsTable
usdAtmPvcStatisticsTable.description: This table contains statistics for PVC entries.

usdAtmPvcStatisticsEntry.name: usdAtmPvcStatisticsEntry
usdAtmPvcStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry provides statistics on an ATM PVC.

usdAtmPvcStatsIfIndex.name: usdAtmPvcStatsIfIndex
usdAtmPvcStatsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface.

usdAtmPvcStatsVpi.name: usdAtmPvcStatsVpi
usdAtmPvcStatsVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

usdAtmPvcStatsVci.name: usdAtmPvcStatsVci
usdAtmPvcStatsVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

usdAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors.name: usdAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors
usdAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors.description: Received cells dropped due to errors.

usdAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors.name: usdAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors
usdAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors.description: Received packets dropped due to errors.

usdAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors.name: usdAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors
usdAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors.description: Cells not transmitted due to errors.

usdAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors.name: usdAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors
usdAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors.description: Packets not transmitted due to errors.

usdAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.name: usdAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol
usdAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.description: Received packets that are discarded because the interface can not discern or is not configured to support this protocol.

usdAtmVpTunnelTable.name: usdAtmVpTunnelTable
usdAtmVpTunnelTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VP Tunnels present in the system.

usdAtmVpTunnelEntry.name: usdAtmVpTunnelEntry
usdAtmVpTunnelEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM VP Tunnel.

usdAtmVpTunnelIfIndex.name: usdAtmVpTunnelIfIndex
usdAtmVpTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. The value of this object is the same as the usdAtmIfIndex object in the usdAtmIfTable. Entries in this table cannot be created unless the underlying ATM interface entry is created first in the usdAtmIfTable.

usdAtmVpTunnelVpi.name: usdAtmVpTunnelVpi
usdAtmVpTunnelVpi.description: The VPI value for this VP tunnel entry.

usdAtmVpTunnelKbps.name: usdAtmVpTunnelKbps
usdAtmVpTunnelKbps.description: The tunnel rate in kilobits per second (kbps) for this entry.

usdAtmVpTunnelRowStatus.name: usdAtmVpTunnelRowStatus
usdAtmVpTunnelRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdAtmVpTunnelRowStatus usdAtmVpTunnelKbps In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A correponding usdAtmVpTunnelIfIndex value must have been created in the usdAtmIfTable previously.

usdAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory.name: usdAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory
usdAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory.description: The ATM service category for the tunnel.

usdAtmIfCapabilityTable.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityTable
usdAtmIfCapabilityTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM interfaces present in the system.

usdAtmIfCapabilityEntry.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityEntry
usdAtmIfCapabilityEntry.description: Each entry describes the capabilities of an ATM interface. A management client can use this table to determine differences in the configurable level of support across entries in this table.

usdAtmIfCapabilityIndex.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityIndex
usdAtmIfCapabilityIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. The value of this object is the same as usdAtmIfIndex in the usdAtmIfTable.

usdAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping
usdAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping.description: Indicates whether traffic shaping is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

usdAtmIfCapabilityOam.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityOam
usdAtmIfCapabilityOam.description: Indicates whether OAM is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

usdAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp
usdAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp.description: The default number of VCs per VP for this interface.

usdAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits
usdAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits.description: The total range of bits used for constructing VPI/VCI identifiers for this interface.

usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd
usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd.description: The maximum configurable value for a VCD on this interface.

usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi
usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi.description: The maximum configurable value for a VPI on this interface.

usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci
usdAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci.description: The maximum configurable value for a VCI on this interface.

usdAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter.name: usdAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter
usdAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter.description: Indicates whether OAM cell filter is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingTable.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingTable
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the usdAtmIfTable for configuring signalling information for switched virtual connection (SVC).

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for ATM signalling on the interface.

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi.description: The VPI identifier of the ATM circuit used for signalling for this interface.

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVci.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVci
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVci.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit used for signalling for this interface.

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit used for signalling for this interface.

usdAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus.name: usdAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus
usdAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of signalling in the ATM interface.

A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdAtmAal5IfTable.name: usdAtmAal5IfTable
usdAtmAal5IfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM AAL5 interfaces present in the system.

usdAtmAal5IfEntry.name: usdAtmAal5IfEntry
usdAtmAal5IfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM AAL5 interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdAtmAal5IfIndex.name: usdAtmAal5IfIndex
usdAtmAal5IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM AAL5 interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdAtmAal5NextIfIndex.

usdAtmAal5IfRowStatus.name: usdAtmAal5IfRowStatus
usdAtmAal5IfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdAtmAal5IfRowStatus usdAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for usdAtmAal5IfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdAtmAal5NextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex.name: usdAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex
usdAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an ATM interface over which this ATM AAL5 interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdAtmSubIfNextIfIndex.name: usdAtmSubIfNextIfIndex
usdAtmSubIfNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdAtmSubIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdAtmSubIfTable.name: usdAtmSubIfTable
usdAtmSubIfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM Subinterfaces present in the system.

usdAtmSubIfEntry.name: usdAtmSubIfEntry
usdAtmSubIfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM Subinterface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdAtmSubIfIndex.name: usdAtmSubIfIndex
usdAtmSubIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM Subinterface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdAtmSubNextIfIndex.

usdAtmSubIfRowStatus.name: usdAtmSubIfRowStatus
usdAtmSubIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdAtmSubIfRowStatus usdAtmSubIfLowerIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for usdAtmSubIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdAtmSubIfNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdAtmSubIfDistinguisher.name: usdAtmSubIfDistinguisher
usdAtmSubIfDistinguisher.description: An integer identifier for the subinterface, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. It is provided here for cross-reference purposes only. The value must be unique among subinterfaces configured on the same underlying ATM adaptation layer. The upper bound for the value is further constrained to be identical with the maximum number of subinterfaces supported by the lower interface. If this object is not configured, a value will be allocated internally and can be queried after table entry creation has succeeded.

usdAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex
usdAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an ATM AAL5 interface over which this ATM subinterface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdAtmSubIfNbma.name: usdAtmSubIfNbma
usdAtmSubIfNbma.description: The NBMA administrative setting. Setting this value of this object to true(1) will enable multipoint access on this interface. Setting the value to false(2), will enable point to point access on this interface.

usdAtmSubIfAddress.name: usdAtmSubIfAddress
usdAtmSubIfAddress.description: Specifies the local ATM NSAP address of the circuit. A GET operation returns a full 20-octet NSAP. A SET operation only requires 7 octets, since the prefix can be implied.

usdAtmSubIfVccTable.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTable
usdAtmSubIfVccTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VCCs configured on ATM subinterfaces present in the system. An implementation may constrain the number of VCCs permitted to be configured per ATM Subinterface; in particular, an implementation may restrict each ATM Subinterface to have a single VCC. Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

usdAtmSubIfVccEntry.name: usdAtmSubIfVccEntry
usdAtmSubIfVccEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM subinterface VCC.

usdAtmSubIfVccVpi.name: usdAtmSubIfVccVpi
usdAtmSubIfVccVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this subinterface.

usdAtmSubIfVccVci.name: usdAtmSubIfVccVci
usdAtmSubIfVccVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this subinterface.

usdAtmSubIfVccRowStatus.name: usdAtmSubIfVccRowStatus
usdAtmSubIfVccRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdAtmSubIfVccRowStatus In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: The ATM Subinterface identified by usdAtmSubIfIndex must exist. A positive value configured for usdAtmSubIfVccVcd must not already be assigned to an existing VCC. For each value of usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory, additional dependent objects in the entry require configuration as identified here: usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory Requires configuration of: ------------------------------------------------------------ ubr <none> ubrPcr usdAtmSubIfVccPcr nrtVbr usdAtmSubIfVccPcr usdAtmSubIfVccScr usdAtmSubIfVccMbs cbr usdAtmSubIfVccPcr rtVbr usdAtmSubIfVccPcr usdAtmSubIfVccScr usdAtmSubIfVccMbs ------------------------------------------------------------ Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

usdAtmSubIfVccVcd.name: usdAtmSubIfVccVcd
usdAtmSubIfVccVcd.description: An integer identifier for the circuit, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. It is provided here for cross-reference purposes only. The value must be unique among VCCs configured on the same underlying ATM interface. If this object is not configured, or is configured with a value of zero, a value will be allocated internally and can be queried after table entry creation has succeeded.

usdAtmSubIfVccType.name: usdAtmSubIfVccType
usdAtmSubIfVccType.description: Specifies the encapsulation used by the circuit to carry IP datagrams. Encapsulations are as specified in RFC1483 Multiprotocol Interconnect over ATM. 'autoconfig' will recognize both VcMux and LLC formats.

usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory.name: usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory
usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory.description: Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified Bit Rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-RealTime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant Bit Rate. rtVbr Realtime Variable Bit Rate.

usdAtmSubIfVccPcr.name: usdAtmSubIfVccPcr
usdAtmSubIfVccPcr.description: Peak Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have one of the following values: ubrPcr nrtVbr cbr rtVbr

usdAtmSubIfVccScr.name: usdAtmSubIfVccScr
usdAtmSubIfVccScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

usdAtmSubIfVccMbs.name: usdAtmSubIfVccMbs
usdAtmSubIfVccMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

usdAtmSubIfInverseArp.name: usdAtmSubIfInverseArp
usdAtmSubIfInverseArp.description: Enables the inverse ARP protocol on this VCC; true(1) enables the protocol, false(2) disables it.

usdAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh.name: usdAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh
usdAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh.description: The refresh rate in minutes between inverse ARP protocol messages.

usdAtmCircuitOamTable.name: usdAtmCircuitOamTable
usdAtmCircuitOamTable.description: This table contains circuit OAM data for a PVC.

usdAtmCircuitOamEntry.name: usdAtmCircuitOamEntry
usdAtmCircuitOamEntry.description: Each entry provides OAM data on an ATM PVC.

usdAtmCircuitOamIfIndex.name: usdAtmCircuitOamIfIndex
usdAtmCircuitOamIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM subinterface.

usdAtmCircuitOamVpi.name: usdAtmCircuitOamVpi
usdAtmCircuitOamVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

usdAtmCircuitOamVci.name: usdAtmCircuitOamVci
usdAtmCircuitOamVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

usdAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus.name: usdAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus
usdAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of OAM for the interface identified by this entry.

usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus.name: usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus
usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus.description: The operational status of OAM for the interface identified by this entry. oamOperStatusNotSupported(0) - OAM not supported on this interface oamOperStatusDisabled(1) - VC integrity disabled oamOperStatusSent(2) - Loopback sent, awaiting response oamOperStatusReceived(3) - Loopback response received, awaiting frequency oamOperStatusFailed(4) - Loopback response not received, or invalid response received

usdAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus.name: usdAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus
usdAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus.description: The OAM VC operational status of this entry. oamVcOperStateAisState(0) - AIS cell received or underlying physical layer reporting transmission path AIS oamVcOperStateRdiState(1) - RDI cell received oamVcOperStateDownRetry(2) - OAM loopback failed, using retry frequency to verify that the VC is really down oamVcOperStateUpRetry(3) - OAM loopback successful, using retry frequency to verify that the VC is really up oamVcOperStateUp(4) - OAM loopback successful after up retry verification oamVcOperStateDown(5) - OAM loopback failed after down retry verification oamVcOperStateNotManaged(6)- No verification via loopback cells being performed.

usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency.name: usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency
usdAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency.description: The OAM loopback frequency for the interface identified by this entry.

usdAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped.name: usdAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped
usdAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped.description: Received OAM cells that were dropped.

usdAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCell.name: usdAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCells
usdAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCell.description: Received OAM F5 end-to-end loopback cells.

usdAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells.name: usdAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells
usdAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells.description: Received OAM F5 segment loopback cells.

usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCel.name: usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCells
usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCel.description: Transmitted OAM F5 end-to-end loopback cells.

usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCell.name: usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells
usdAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCell.description: Transmitted OAM F5 segment loopback cells.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable.description: This table contains entries for traffic shaping of ATM VCCs configured on ATM subinterfaces present in the system. This table augments the usdAtmSubIfVccTable only for VCCs that support traffic shapping. Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry.description: Each entry describes the traffic shping characteristics of an ATM subinterface VCC.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt.description: The network cell delay variation tolerance (CDVT) in tenths of a microsecond.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0.description: Specifies whether or not only CLP0 cells are to be policed according to the traffic contract. CLP1 cells are forwarded on a best-effort basis CLP-significant model for (VBR.2, VBR.3 conformance). Applicable only for VBR circuits.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging.description: Specifies whether or not CLP0 cells should be tagged for SCR policing (VBR.3 conformance). Applicable only for VBR circuits.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObserv.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObserve
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObserv.description: Specifies whether of not no policing action is to be taken (note the double negative; if true(1) then no policing action will be taken; if false(2) then policing action will be taken). Regardless of the state of this object, all counters will be incremented.

usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShapin.name: usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShaping
usdAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShapin.description: Specifies whether of not to shape output traffic on a packet boundary.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the usdAtmSubIfTable to configure switched virtual connection (SVC)on the subinterfaces.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for an ATM SVC on the subinterface.

usdAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus
usdAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress.description: Specifies the destination ATM NSAP address of the circuit.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType.description: Specifies the encapsulation used by the circuit to carry IP datagrams. Encapsulations are as specified in RFC1483 Multiprotocol Interconnect over ATM.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory.description: Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified Bit Rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-RealTime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant Bit Rate. rtVbr Realtime Variable Bit Rate.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr.description: Peak Cell Rate, in kilo-bits per second (kbps), of this circuit.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilo-bits per second (kbps), of this circuit.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt.description: Specify the network Cell Delay Variation Tolerance.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0.description: Specify that only CLP0 cells are to be policed according to the traffic contract. CLP1 cells are forwarded on a best-effort basis CLP-significant model for (VBR.2, VBR.3 conformance).

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging.description: Specify that CLP0 cells should be tagged for SCR policing (VBR.3 conformance).

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve.description: Specify that no policing action is to be taken; only counters are incremented.

usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard.name: usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard
usdAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard.description: Enable early packet Discard for this circuit.

usdAtmNbmaMapTable.name: usdAtmNbmaMapTable
usdAtmNbmaMapTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM NBMA maps.

usdAtmNbmaMapEntry.name: usdAtmNbmaMapEntry
usdAtmNbmaMapEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM NBMA map.

usdAtmNbmaMapVcd.name: usdAtmNbmaMapVcd
usdAtmNbmaMapVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ATM circuit, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. The value must be unique among VCs configured on the same ATM interface.

usdAtmNbmaMapIpAddress.name: usdAtmNbmaMapIpAddress
usdAtmNbmaMapIpAddress.description: The IP address associated with this entry.

usdAtmNbmaMapVpi.name: usdAtmNbmaMapVpi
usdAtmNbmaMapVpi.description: The VPI identifier of the ATM circuit.

usdAtmNbmaMapVci.name: usdAtmNbmaMapVci
usdAtmNbmaMapVci.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit.

usdAtmNbmaMapIfIndex.name: usdAtmNbmaMapIfIndex
usdAtmNbmaMapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM major interface associated with this entry. The value of this object will be zero when the map is not applied to an interface.

usdAtmNbmaMapBroadcast.name: usdAtmNbmaMapBroadcast
usdAtmNbmaMapBroadcast.description: The broadcast enable/disable setting for this entry. The value true(1) enable broadcast support; disable(2) disabled broadcast support for this entry.

usdAtmNbmaMapRowStatus.name: usdAtmNbmaMapRowStatus
usdAtmNbmaMapRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy Additional notes to aid the network manager: - NBMA maps are not supported on dynamic interface. - NBMA maps can only be applied to a single major ATM interface at a time. - NBMA maps cannot be deleted unless the map is removed from the ATM interface (usdAtmNbmaMapIfIndex = 0). - The values of usdAtmNbmaMapVpi, usdAtmNbmaMapVci and usdAtmNbmaMapIfIndex are zero until the map is applied to a major ATM interface. - To create an entry in this table, the following objects must be present in the set PDU: usdAtmNbmaMapIpAddress usdAtmNbmaMapBroadcast usdAtmNbmaMapRowStatus - Once created, only the following objects can be modified: usdAtmNbmaMapBroadcast

usdAtmNbmaMapListTable.name: usdAtmNbmaMapListTable
usdAtmNbmaMapListTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM NBMA map lists.

usdAtmNbmaMapListEntry.name: usdAtmNbmaMapListEntry
usdAtmNbmaMapListEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM NBMA map.

usdAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus.name: usdAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus
usdAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

usdAtmPingTestOamSeg.name: usdAtmPingTestOamSeg
usdAtmPingTestOamSeg.description: This identifies an OAM Ping (multiple loopbacks) Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using segment OAM cells. The test type must have appended to it a code that uniquely identifies an intermediate point responsible for looping back each cell. If this is absent, the loopbacks are performed at the end of the segment or connection. E.g., the OID { usdAtmPingTestOamSeg 5 } identifies that the loopbacks should be performed at the intermediate point labeled 5.

usdAtmPingTestOamE2E.name: usdAtmPingTestOamE2E
usdAtmPingTestOamE2E.description: This identifies an OAM Ping (multiple loopbacks) Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using end-to-end OAM cells.

usdAtmVpPingTable.name: usdAtmVpPingTable
usdAtmVpPingTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the ATM-FORUM-SNMP-M4-MIB atmM4VpTestTable to do ping (multiple loopback) type testing.

usdAtmVpPingEntry.name: usdAtmVpPingEntry
usdAtmVpPingEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics, status and results of the most recent ATM ping test.

usdAtmVpPingProbeCount.name: usdAtmVpPingProbeCount
usdAtmVpPingProbeCount.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) to be sent to complete the test.

usdAtmVpPingTimeOut.name: usdAtmVpPingTimeOut
usdAtmVpPingTimeOut.description: Specifies the time-out value, in seconds, for a remote ping operation.

usdAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration.name: usdAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration
usdAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration.description: The value of this object determines when and if to generate a notification for this entry: testCompletion(0) - Generate a usdPingTestCompleted notification. The value of this object defaults to zero, indicating that no notification has been selected.

usdAtmVpPingSentProbes.name: usdAtmVpPingSentProbes
usdAtmVpPingSentProbes.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) that have been sent thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

usdAtmVpPingProbeResponses.name: usdAtmVpPingProbeResponses
usdAtmVpPingProbeResponses.description: The number of ping responses that have been received thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

usdAtmVpPingStartTime.name: usdAtmVpPingStartTime
usdAtmVpPingStartTime.description: The time (sysUpTime) when the test started.

usdAtmVpPingMinRtt.name: usdAtmVpPingMinRtt
usdAtmVpPingMinRtt.description: The shortest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVpPingMaxRtt.name: usdAtmVpPingMaxRtt
usdAtmVpPingMaxRtt.description: The longest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVpPingAverageRtt.name: usdAtmVpPingAverageRtt
usdAtmVpPingAverageRtt.description: The average round-trip-time (RTT) for all the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVcPingTable.name: usdAtmVcPingTable

usdAtmVcPingEntry.name: usdAtmVcPingEntry
usdAtmVcPingEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics, status and results of the most recent ATM ping test.

usdAtmVcPingProbeCount.name: usdAtmVcPingProbeCount
usdAtmVcPingProbeCount.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) to be sent to complete the test.

usdAtmVcPingTimeOut.name: usdAtmVcPingTimeOut
usdAtmVcPingTimeOut.description: Specifies the time-out value, in seconds, for a remote ping operation.

usdAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration.name: usdAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration
usdAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration.description: The value of this object determines when and if to generate a notification for this entry: testCompletion(0) - Generate a usdPingTestCompleted notification. The value of this object defaults to zero, indicating that no notification has been selected.

usdAtmVcPingSentProbes.name: usdAtmVcPingSentProbes
usdAtmVcPingSentProbes.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) that have been sent thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

usdAtmVcPingProbeResponses.name: usdAtmVcPingProbeResponses
usdAtmVcPingProbeResponses.description: The number of ping responses that have been received thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

usdAtmVcPingStartTime.name: usdAtmVcPingStartTime
usdAtmVcPingStartTime.description: The time (sysUpTime) when the test started.

usdAtmVcPingMinRtt.name: usdAtmVcPingMinRtt
usdAtmVcPingMinRtt.description: The shortest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVcPingMaxRtt.name: usdAtmVcPingMaxRtt
usdAtmVcPingMaxRtt.description: The longest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVcPingAverageRtt.name: usdAtmVcPingAverageRtt
usdAtmVcPingAverageRtt.description: The average round-trip-time (RTT) for all the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

usdAtmVpPingTestCompleted.name: usdAtmVpPingTestCompleted
usdAtmVpPingTestCompleted.description: Generated at the completion of a AtmfM4VpTest when the corresponding usdAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration object has the testCompletion(0) bit set.

usdAtmVcPingTestCompleted.name: usdAtmVcPingTestCompleted
usdAtmVcPingTestCompleted.description: Generated at the completion of a AtmfM4VcTest when the corresponding usdAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration object has the testCompletion(0) bit set.
